<subSubSection pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Habit and distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Shrubs; northern and western Madagascar (Antsiranana, Mahajanga).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="41" lastPageNumber="42" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="41" lastPageNumber="42" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
We follow here the precedent of 
<bibRefCitation author="Leandri, J" journalOrPublisher="Candollea" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" refId="B35" refString="Leandri, J, 1939. Les Croton de Madagascar et des iles voisines. Annales du Musee Colonial de Marseille, ser. 5, 7 (1): 1-100." title="Les Croton de Madagascar et des iles voisines. Annales du Musee Colonial de Marseille, ser. 5, 7 (1): 1 - 100." year="1939">Leandri (1939)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Radcliffe-Smith, A" journalOrPublisher="Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" refId="B55" refString="Radcliffe-Smith, A, 2016. The Genus Croton in Madagascar &amp; the Comoro Is. Received at Kew, NHM and RHS Wisley libraries as a pre-print on 23 Dec 2016 via Martin Cheek, 1-213." title="The Genus Croton in Madagascar &amp; the Comoro Is. Received at Kew, NHM and RHS Wisley libraries as a pre-print on 23 Dec 2016 via Martin Cheek, 1 - 213." year="2016">Radcliffe-Smith (2016)</bibRefCitation>
in treating 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Croton squamiger" order="Malpighiales" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="squamiger">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Croton squamiger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. jennyanus" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" rank="species" species="jennyanus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">C. jennyanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but we differ in treating 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. hypochalibaeus" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" rank="species" species="hypochalibaeus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">C. hypochalibaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a distinct, more highland species rather than as another 
<pageBreakToken pageId="41" pageNumber="42" start="start">synonym</pageBreakToken>
of 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. jennyanus" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" rank="species" species="jennyanus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">C. jennyanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.15553/c2016v712a17" author="Kainulainen, K" journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" refId="B29" refString="Kainulainen, K, Van Ee, B, Antilahimena, P, Razafindraibe, H, Berry, PE, 2016. New species and species reports of Croton (Euphorbiaceae) from the eastern forest corridor of Madagascar. Candollea 71: 327-356. https://doi.org/10.15553/c2016v712a17" title="New species and species reports of Croton (Euphorbiaceae) from the eastern forest corridor of Madagascar. Candollea 71: 327 - 356." url="https://doi.org/10.15553/c2016v712a17" year="2016">Kainulainen et al., 2016</bibRefCitation>
). According to our interpretation, 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. jennyanus" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" rank="species" species="jennyanus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">C. jennyanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to lower elevations in northern Madagascar (Montagne des 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Français">Francais</normalizedToken>
, Sahafary, Daraina, Ankarana), as well as in far midwestern Madagascar on or near tsingy formations (Bemaraha).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
Concerning the type of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Croton squamiger" order="Malpighiales" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="squamiger">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Croton squamiger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, three other sheets of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Boivin 2658</emphasis>
correspond to 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. brevispicatus" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" rank="species" species="brevispicatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">C. brevispicatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, so this is clearly a mixed collection. In the description of 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. squamiger" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" rank="species" species="squamiger">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">C. squamiger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Baillon, H" journalOrPublisher="Adansonia" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" pagination="139 - 173" refId="B3" refString="Baillon, H, 1861. Euphorbiacees Africaines. Deuxieme Partie, Afrique Orientale (Bourbon, Maurice, Madagascar, Zanguebar, etc.). Adansonia 1: 139 - 173" title="Euphorbiacees Africaines. Deuxieme Partie, Afrique Orientale (Bourbon, Maurice, Madagascar, Zanguebar, etc.)." volume="1" year="1861">Baillon (1861)</bibRefCitation>
divided the species into two infraspecific taxa, a and b. These were subsequently named by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mueller, J" editor="Candolle, AP de" journalOrPublisher="Paris, Strasbourg, &amp; London" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="189 - 1261" refId="B51" refString="Mueller, J, 1866. Euphorbiaceae. In: Candolle, AP de, Ed., Prodromus systematis naturalis regni vegetabilis 15(2). Paris, Strasbourg, &amp; London: 189 - 1261" title="Euphorbiaceae." volumeTitle="Prodromus systematis naturalis regni vegetabilis 15 (2)." year="1866">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Müller">Mueller</normalizedToken>
(1866)
</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. squamigerus subsp. var. var. obtusifolius" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" rank="variety" species="squamigerus" subSpecies="var." variety="obtusifolius">C. squamigerus var. obtusifolius</taxonomicName>
(the typical variety) and 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. squamigerus subsp. var. var. acutifolius" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" rank="variety" species="squamigerus" subSpecies="var." variety="acutifolius">C. squamigerus var. acutifolius</taxonomicName>
, respectively. The latter has been recognized here to be synonymous with 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. hypochalibaeus" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" rank="species" species="hypochalibaeus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">C. hypochalibaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
We have corrected the termination of the specific epithet to &quot; 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Croton squamiger" order="Malpighiales" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="squamiger">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Croton squamiger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; [masc. gender, Adj. group A nom., see 
<bibRefCitation author="Stearn, WT" journalOrPublisher="Candollea" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" refId="B58" refString="Stearn, WT, 1992. Botanical Latin : history, grammar, syntax, terminology and vocabulary. 4th ed. Newton Abbot, UK, 1-546." title="Botanical Latin: history, grammar, syntax, terminology and vocabulary. 4 th ed. Newton Abbot, UK, 1 - 546." year="1992">Stearn (1992</bibRefCitation>
: 91) and Art. 23.5 and Art. 60.9 Ex. 24 (
<bibRefCitation author="ICN" journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" refId="B28" refString="ICN, 2012. International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Melbourne Code). Koeltz Scientific Books, Oberreifenberg, Germany." title="International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Melbourne Code). Koeltz Scientific Books, Oberreifenberg, Germany." year="2012">ICN 2012</bibRefCitation>
; 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Croton ciliato-glanduliferum" order="Malpighiales" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ciliato-glanduliferum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Croton ciliato-glanduliferum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Ortega corrected to 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. ciliatoglandulifer" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" rank="species" species="ciliatoglandulifer">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">C. ciliatoglandulifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<bibRefCitation author="Radcliffe-Smith, A" journalOrPublisher="Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" refId="B55" refString="Radcliffe-Smith, A, 2016. The Genus Croton in Madagascar &amp; the Comoro Is. Received at Kew, NHM and RHS Wisley libraries as a pre-print on 23 Dec 2016 via Martin Cheek, 1-213." title="The Genus Croton in Madagascar &amp; the Comoro Is. Received at Kew, NHM and RHS Wisley libraries as a pre-print on 23 Dec 2016 via Martin Cheek, 1 - 213." year="2016">Radcliffe-Smith (2016)</bibRefCitation>
listed 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Croton jennyanus" order="Malpighiales" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jennyanus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Croton jennyanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as being present in the Comoros Archipelago. The three collections he cited [
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Pascal 928</emphasis>
(K, P) from Mayotte, and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Floret 1241</emphasis>
(P) and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">1249</emphasis>
(P) from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Mohéli">Moheli</normalizedToken>
] all correspond to 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. humblotii" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" rank="species" species="humblotii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">C. humblotii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
